    "plan_content": "Here's the full implementation plan — ready for your approval before any code is touched.\n\n---\n\n## Plan Summary: Add `ollama rename`\n\n**4 files to modify, zero new files.**\n\n### What changes where\n\n| File | What's added |\n|---|---|\n| `api/types.go` | `RenameRequest{Source, Destination string}` struct (after `CopyRequest` at line 765) |\n| `api/client.go` | `Client.Rename()` method (after `Copy()` at line 388), calls `POST /api/rename` |\n| `server/routes.go` | `RenameHandler` func (after `CopyHandler` at line 1483) + route registration next to `/api/copy` |\n| `cmd/cmd.go` | `RenameHandler` CLI func (after `CopyHandler` at line 1351), `renameCmd` cobra command, added to `rootCmd.AddCommand` |\n\n### Handler logic (the core)\n1. Bind JSON → 400 on bad/missing body\n2. `model.ParseName(source)` → 400 if invalid; canonicalise with `getExistingName`\n3. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → **404** if source doesn't exist\n4. `model.ParseName(destination)` → 400 if invalid; canonicalise with `getExistingName`\n5. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` — if this **succeeds**, destination already exists → **409**\n6. `CopyModel(src, dst)` — copies the manifest file (blobs are content-addressed, shared)\n7. `srcManifest.Remove()` — removes source manifest only (no `RemoveLayers()` needed; destination now owns the same blobs)\n8. Return 200 empty body\n\n### Key design notes\n- **Same-name case** (rename X to X): step 5 finds the destination manifest already exists → 409, no mutation occurs\n- **Why not `RemoveLayers()`**: after copy the destination manifest references all blobs, so none are orphaned — calling `RemoveLayers()` would scan everything and delete nothing; `Remove()` alone is correct\n- **Why `model.ParseName` not `parseNormalizePullModelRef`**: rename is a pure local operation, same as copy; no cloud source parsing needed\n- **All existing functions reused**: `getExistingName`, `manifest.ParseNamedManifest`, `CopyModel`, `srcManifest.Remove()` — no new storage-layer logic",
